You should have received or will be receiving information on registering your student for the upcoming 2020-21 school year. We are asking that all parents go on Skyward and complete this registration by May 18. Step by step instructions have been provided in the information that was mailed. Please pay particular attention to item 1.c Family Information. The phone numbers need to be entered correctly for our global calling system that we use to send out messages regarding school delays, closings and other important information. If you need help registering your student for next school year, please contact your child's school office. It is very important that you complete this registration by May 18, 2020.

Thank you.

Seniors can pick up their cap and gown on May 14, 2020 in the front parking lot of the high school from 2:00PM-4:00PM. Any other graduation products including announcements or other items will be available for pickup at this time. Jostens will be sending out postcards with any balance due that needs to be paid at pickup. Please try and have exact change when paying at the school. Only cash payments will be accepted on-site. If you need to pay with a credit or debit card, please call the Jostens office prior to May 14, 2020. The Jostens office number is 317-326-2782.

If you have any questions regarding cap and gown pickup, please contact the high school office.

post_text: This past Saturday the Eastbrook FFA participated in the State Small Engines contest at the Central Nine Career Center in Greenwood Indiana. Dillon Embry & Jarod Voris placed 2nd in the state. AJ Stinger & Jeffery Duckwall placed 3rd in the state. They missed first place by 9 points and only 5.5 points separated the two teams from Eastbrook. This is the first time that Eastbrook has ever had two teams place in the top four of any state contest at the same time.
